body:
@iemejia @jbonofre 
I believe users/developers should either install the specific version of gradle (4.2.1) that this build uses or should rely on using the gradle wrapper script. I would like to defer upgrading to gradle 4.3 to another PR.

@jbonofre 
For the part of maven enforcer which prevents certain dependencies, I just ban them globally here:
https://github.com/lukecwik/incubator-beam/blob/8ca3fdca276a74973cd428d7321b995f7b7ebccf/build_rules.gradle#L172
I found http://www.mojohaus.org/extra-enforcer-rules/dependency-info.html but have yet to configure it.

@iemejia , you're right, I was doing it while familiarizing myself with the code. And technically speaking it probably is not needed for the implementation of SQL. My reasoning was that it would be a good opportunity to address few issues while I'm at it.

But I feel it is necessary to refactor this at some point anyway. [This class](https://github.com/apache/beam/blob/64ff21f35ee2946d38645fb0a51678628e49e62a/sdks/java/nexmark/src/main/java/org/apache/beam/sdk/nexmark/NexmarkLauncher.java) is 1157 lines of procedural code, with methods of 100+ lines long, with minimal logical structure. And it has zero test coverage from what I see. It is hard to follow, modify and debug.

If there's an opposition to this amount of changes at once, then I can drop this for now and try to add new features to existing code in smaller chunks.
